Today is the 9th anniversary of the death of main Bitcoin pioneer Hal Finney

On 28 August 2014, the famous cryptographer and supporter of Bitcoin, Hal Finney, who played a crucial role in the history of the first cryptocurrency, died. Now he would be 67 years old.

Hal was the first person to launch a Bitcoin node since Satoshi Nakamoto, which marked the beginning of the network's expansion. He also wrote about this in his tweet "Running bitcoin".

He became the recipient of the first BTC transaction from Satoshi, and, according to one version, he himself may be the creator of Bitcoin.
